<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="403">
etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole crinita Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole crinita Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinita">crinita</taxonomicName>
, hairy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="403">
Diagnosis a small, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group distinguished in the major and minor by the complete absence of sculpturing posterior to the level of the eye, broadly concave occipital border, nearly perfect semicircular profde of the promesonotum, and abundant, long pilosity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="403">
Major: nearly vertical propodeal spine in side view, exceptionally large propodeal spiracle, and laterally angulate postpetiolar node. Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181837" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">amabilis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181845" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana">boliviana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181899" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melastomae">melastomae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181905" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixteca">mixteca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181940" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scitula Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scitula Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scitula">scitula</taxonomicName>
, and especially 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34052" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terresi">terresi</taxonomicName>
of Hispaniola and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34074" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tysoni Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tysoni Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tysoni">tysoni</taxonomicName>
of the eastern United States.
</paragraph>
